  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The pump is operated by perfusionists during CPB procedures; all validation activities assume correctly specified boundary conditions and nominal flow-speed inputs. No operator misuse scenarios, input-entry errors, or training-gap effects are characterized anywhere in the evidence package.",
